00:29:49.760 --> 00:29:55.070
So that's telling the stories
of the people in Burma and

00:29:55.070 --> 00:29:57.845
along its borders and helping
to get support.

00:30:00.660 --> 00:30:03.710
I want to tell you a little bit
about how I got involved

00:30:03.710 --> 00:30:05.050
and then how if you're

00:30:05.050 --> 00:30:07.090
interested you can get involved.

00:30:07.090 --> 00:30:09.090
So not too long ago I
was a journalist.

00:30:09.090 --> 00:30:11.130
I had a long career
as a journalist.

00:30:11.130 --> 00:30:13.130
But I also had a secret life.

00:30:13.130 --> 00:30:17.015
And that was volunteering with
my husband, who's a doctor, at

00:30:17.015 --> 00:30:19.990
a refugee clinic run
by a really amazing

00:30:19.990 --> 00:30:22.090
woman refugee doctor.

00:30:22.090 --> 00:30:25.330
And while we were there--
this is back in 1996--

00:30:25.330 --> 00:30:28.990
we crossed the border from
Thailand in a pickup truck at

00:30:28.990 --> 00:30:33.280
night over the hills to
a little village in

00:30:33.280 --> 00:30:35.920
rebel-controlled Burma, where
they hadn't seen of

00:30:35.920 --> 00:30:38.080
pediatrician in years.

00:30:38.080 --> 00:30:42.860
And I fell in love with the
children, playing with them.

00:30:42.860 --> 00:30:44.990
And these are two of the
girls, [? Shua ?]

00:30:44.990 --> 00:30:50.650
and [? Omoo ?], and all the kids
were really delightful.

00:30:50.650 --> 00:30:52.810
These two were good friends in
particular, and in fact they

00:30:52.810 --> 00:30:53.810
were in preschool.

00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:56.473
So you heard about the
importance of preschools, and

00:30:56.473 --> 00:30:58.430
they used to sing
the ABC song.

00:30:58.430 --> 00:31:01.250
Anyway, after my year off--

00:31:01.250 --> 00:31:04.210
I had taken a sabbatical
for my job--

00:31:04.210 --> 00:31:08.470
we came back to Seattle where we
live, and then I found out

00:31:08.470 --> 00:31:13.540
that the village had fallen
to the military.

00:31:13.540 --> 00:31:17.610
It was just my heart, you know
that something had happened.

00:31:17.610 --> 00:31:20.960
So I convinced the newspaper to
send me back on a special

00:31:20.960 --> 00:31:24.890
assignment, and I was trying
to find the girls.

00:31:24.890 --> 00:31:26.130
I didn't tell the
newspaper that.

00:31:26.130 --> 00:31:28.340
I said I was going to write
about the civil war in Burma.

00:31:28.340 --> 00:31:33.370
And I couldn't get to them
because there was this war.

00:31:33.370 --> 00:31:36.190
But over the years I kept trying
to get contact and I

00:31:36.190 --> 00:31:36.930
would hear things.

00:31:36.930 --> 00:31:42.140
And as they grew up,
what happened.

00:31:42.140 --> 00:31:45.760
Their village was occupied
by enemy soldiers, right?

00:31:45.760 --> 00:31:46.960
They were very poor.

00:31:46.960 --> 00:31:50.170
One of them was an orphan, so
all of these factors made them

00:31:50.170 --> 00:31:51.300
so vulnerable.

00:31:51.300 --> 00:31:54.330
And like so many other
girls, so vulnerable.

00:31:54.330 --> 00:31:56.600
Would they leave the village
to try to find work?

00:31:56.600 --> 00:31:59.080
Would soldiers try to take
advantage of them?

00:31:59.080 --> 00:32:00.900
What happened?

00:32:00.900 --> 00:32:04.870
So what happened was actually
a really good thing.

00:32:04.870 --> 00:32:06.930
After several years they were
both able to get out of the

00:32:06.930 --> 00:32:12.310
village and get into
boarding school.

00:32:12.310 --> 00:32:14.990
So now they're 20--

00:32:14.990 --> 00:32:17.690
around 19, 20-- one wants to
be a teacher and the other

00:32:17.690 --> 00:32:18.810
wants to be a doctor.

00:32:18.810 --> 00:32:22.060
So it's like oh yeah, that's a
great story, but there are 43

00:32:22.060 --> 00:32:26.820
million people like them who
are displaced still.

00:32:26.820 --> 00:32:30.050
I mean those are two of 43
million who had a good story,

00:32:30.050 --> 00:32:36.530
and so that is why I thought
I've got to do more.

00:32:36.530 --> 00:32:41.140
Anyway, so I got more involved
and I was here in America,

00:32:41.140 --> 00:32:42.950
what can you do here?

00:32:42.950 --> 00:32:46.920
I got involved with a little
group and we did raffles and

00:32:46.920 --> 00:32:48.020
all kinds of things like.

00:32:48.020 --> 00:32:52.000
That I took ESL courses,
ESL tutoring, and I

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:53.470
went over and I tutored.

00:32:53.470 --> 00:32:56.780
I taught aerobics to refugee
medics over there.

00:32:56.780 --> 00:32:59.320
And in America went and told
people about Burma.

00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:00.040
I wrote about it.

00:33:00.040 --> 00:33:01.920
Those happened to be
my skill sets.

00:33:01.920 --> 00:33:03.140
You have other skill sets.

00:33:03.140 --> 00:33:08.360
So here are 12 ways to get
involved if you're interested.

00:33:08.360 --> 00:33:09.640
Share your expertise.

00:33:09.640 --> 00:33:12.860
I know a lot of people have
expertise here in technology.

00:33:12.860 --> 00:33:17.780
One of our colleagues is doing
really interesting project,

00:33:17.780 --> 00:33:22.930
trying to get it off the ground
with using phones,

00:33:22.930 --> 00:33:27.830
interactive voice recognition,
to provide health care

00:33:27.830 --> 00:33:31.110
information to people
on the move.

00:33:31.110 --> 00:33:35.170
So that could be trafficked or
migrant people, many of them

00:33:35.170 --> 00:33:39.350
are illiterate, so it's great to
get that information about

00:33:39.350 --> 00:33:42.970
malaria and reproductive
health over the phone.

00:33:42.970 --> 00:33:45.160
But there's solar-powered
phones, there's a lot

00:33:45.160 --> 00:33:46.410
going on with that.

00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:52.650
Something simple for you is
setting up and training using

00:33:52.650 --> 00:33:55.180
Google Apps and other
Google tools.

00:33:55.180 --> 00:33:56.480
At our organization--

00:33:56.480 --> 00:34:00.550
and this is both in the
States here and

00:34:00.550 --> 00:34:01.550
with our local partners.

00:34:01.550 --> 00:34:05.110
I mean, we touch the
Google tools

00:34:05.110 --> 00:34:06.780
and use them so clumsily.

00:34:06.780 --> 00:34:11.150
So just to have somebody kind
of hold our hand and say, OK

00:34:11.150 --> 00:34:13.070
here are your needs, you should
really be using this

00:34:13.070 --> 00:34:14.940
and this is how you do it.

00:34:14.940 --> 00:34:18.949
SCO optimization,
graphic design--

00:34:18.949 --> 00:34:23.572
if there's a website wizard or
goddess who could help, you

00:34:23.572 --> 00:34:26.370
know we use Drupal, that
would be great.

00:34:26.370 --> 00:34:28.850
And not just with our
organization, but any

00:34:28.850 --> 00:34:31.280
organization that does this kind
of thing, share with your

00:34:31.280 --> 00:34:34.120
friends, learn about
trafficking

00:34:34.120 --> 00:34:35.080
or women and girls.

00:34:35.080 --> 00:34:36.710
Whatever your passion is--

00:34:36.710 --> 00:34:38.500
Burma, Nepal--

00:34:38.500 --> 00:34:39.860
and share that with
your friends.

00:34:39.860 --> 00:34:43.469
Host conversations, post, blog,
talk about it, engage

00:34:43.469 --> 00:34:45.310
your network.

00:34:45.310 --> 00:34:48.659
We have wonderful supporters
and donors

00:34:48.659 --> 00:34:54.600
who do a baking book.

00:34:54.600 --> 00:34:56.650
They've done crafts things.

00:34:56.650 --> 00:35:00.160
It doesn't really matter what it
is, the idea is to engage.

00:35:00.160 --> 00:35:03.050
One of our supporters is a
Broadway producer, and she had

00:35:03.050 --> 00:35:04.960
a Broadway bash.

00:35:04.960 --> 00:35:10.820
So it just depends on your
expertise and your contacts.

00:35:10.820 --> 00:35:15.290
Donations are always welcome,
and I know there's an employee

00:35:15.290 --> 00:35:18.110
matching gift, so
that's helpful.

00:35:18.110 --> 00:35:20.680
Online friend-to-friend
fund raising, we're

00:35:20.680 --> 00:35:21.840
starting to do that.

00:35:21.840 --> 00:35:26.450
And if you spend a lot of time
online with your communities

00:35:26.450 --> 00:35:28.720
online, that might
be something to

00:35:28.720 --> 00:35:29.940
get involved with.

00:35:29.940 --> 00:35:33.140
And then there's also travel,
to broaden your horizons and

00:35:33.140 --> 00:35:36.030
look for volunteer
opportunities.

00:35:36.030 --> 00:35:40.240
So thank you very much,
and those are--

