00:39:38.040 --> 00:39:39.410
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:39:39.410 --> 00:39:41.243
THERESE CAOUETTE: OK

00:39:41.243 --> 00:39:43.167
AUDIENCE: You made this
statement already [INAUDIBLE]?

00:40:04.260 --> 00:40:09.730
THERESE CAOUETTE: OK, the
question was, what can men do?

00:40:09.730 --> 00:40:11.840
And if men had a different
attitude, wouldn't some of

00:40:11.840 --> 00:40:13.330
this change?

00:40:13.330 --> 00:40:15.220
And I would say it's yes.

00:40:15.220 --> 00:40:16.170
There's two ways.

00:40:16.170 --> 00:40:18.580
One of the ways-- in the
beginning we focused way too

00:40:18.580 --> 00:40:20.380
much on women and girls.

00:40:20.380 --> 00:40:22.540
And I think what we're learning
too is that this is a

00:40:22.540 --> 00:40:24.990
dynamic and something that
affects the whole community.

00:40:24.990 --> 00:40:26.080
So I say it's both ways.

00:40:26.080 --> 00:40:28.690
I think we too as organizations
have to see this

00:40:28.690 --> 00:40:30.610
as a community issue.

00:40:30.610 --> 00:40:34.340
And I think for men, it's
important for them to speak to

00:40:34.340 --> 00:40:37.160
women's rights.

00:40:37.160 --> 00:40:38.940
What's always the hardest
for me is the

00:40:38.940 --> 00:40:40.680
girls that I work with--

00:40:40.680 --> 00:40:42.020
especially the girls--

00:40:42.020 --> 00:40:45.570
their self esteem is so low
that they actually believe

00:40:45.570 --> 00:40:48.110
that it's their fault that
this has happened.

00:40:48.110 --> 00:40:53.560
So I think promoting and
speaking to women about girls

00:40:53.560 --> 00:40:55.320
and about women in
a positive--

00:40:55.320 --> 00:40:57.950
I think that happens in
our day-to-day life.

00:40:57.950 --> 00:41:01.080
One of the most disturbing
things for me is when Western

00:41:01.080 --> 00:41:06.290
travelers go to Asia and they
are really awful tourists,

00:41:06.290 --> 00:41:07.500
quite frankly.

00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:11.110
It's just disrespectful.

00:41:11.110 --> 00:41:13.940
And then even for myself as a
woman, I don't stand up to it

00:41:13.940 --> 00:41:15.380
as much as they should.

00:41:15.380 --> 00:41:17.590
Sometimes you should really
say something.

00:41:17.590 --> 00:41:20.060
And I think for men to say it
to other men or at least not

00:41:20.060 --> 00:41:20.860
to participate.

00:41:20.860 --> 00:41:24.600
To be not other and to put
yourself in that context.

00:41:24.600 --> 00:41:27.160
I think we all have a
lot of challenges in

00:41:27.160 --> 00:41:29.000
how we "other" people.

00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:31.800
And I would say that both in our
context and also when we

00:41:31.800 --> 00:41:34.290
look abroad that's
a challenge.

