00:45:33.080 --> 00:45:36.750
THERESE CAOUETTE: So the
question is, how do we recover

00:45:36.750 --> 00:45:39.610
or how do we know if people
been able to be tracked or

00:45:39.610 --> 00:45:42.690
returned home after they've
been sent abroad.

00:45:42.690 --> 00:45:45.000
Or after they've gone to look
for work or possibly been

00:45:45.000 --> 00:45:46.470
trafficked.

00:45:46.470 --> 00:45:49.230
And I would say it's incredibly
difficult.

00:45:49.230 --> 00:45:51.890
The most that we can do
is work on both sides.

00:45:51.890 --> 00:45:54.420
We work both on the China side
of the border and the Burma

00:45:54.420 --> 00:45:57.730
side, the Thai side and
the Burma side.

00:45:57.730 --> 00:46:01.330
And through those networks,
we can try to track.

00:46:01.330 --> 00:46:05.660
But it's very, very difficult,
and we have families and

00:46:05.660 --> 00:46:09.560
parents who have been waiting
for their kids for years.

00:46:09.560 --> 00:46:13.880
And I just actually last week
met someone a woman who was

00:46:13.880 --> 00:46:16.130
waiting for her husband to
return yet, She hasn't heard

00:46:16.130 --> 00:46:18.010
from him in three years.

00:46:18.010 --> 00:46:20.670
So she has no idea if he's gone
off on a fishing boat and

00:46:20.670 --> 00:46:24.270
not been allowed to come back to
land, or he's been put in a

00:46:24.270 --> 00:46:25.980
factory or he died.

00:46:25.980 --> 00:46:27.300
She may never know.

00:46:27.300 --> 00:46:34.000
This happens a lot, and it's
very difficult to track,

00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:35.250
unfortunately.

00:46:40.692 --> 00:46:41.942
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]?

00:46:49.060 --> 00:46:52.115
THERESE CAOUETTE: She's asking
reintegrating back home and do

00:46:52.115 --> 00:46:54.980
you see them being trafficked
again or moving again.

00:46:54.980 --> 00:46:56.380
I think is a vicious cycle.

00:46:56.380 --> 00:46:59.110
I think once they've gone
abroad, they come back.

00:46:59.110 --> 00:47:01.590
It's very difficult
to return home.

00:47:01.590 --> 00:47:04.040
There's still no jobs there.

00:47:04.040 --> 00:47:05.520
And that's why I showed
that picture of them

00:47:05.520 --> 00:47:06.800
praying at the shrine.

00:47:06.800 --> 00:47:10.180
They think OK, I'll have a
good prayer and next time

00:47:10.180 --> 00:47:12.560
hopefully I won't have such bad
luck, or I'll have better

00:47:12.560 --> 00:47:14.430
luck and I'll try again.

00:47:14.430 --> 00:47:16.860
And this cycle just
goes on and on.

00:47:16.860 --> 00:47:18.950
About the thing we were talking
about at lunch just

00:47:18.950 --> 00:47:21.860
before I came is it's also it
is very difficult for people

00:47:21.860 --> 00:47:24.880
to get remittances to send
their money back home.

00:47:24.880 --> 00:47:27.040
And this is one of things you're
talking about with the

00:47:27.040 --> 00:47:29.240
new cell phone banking.

00:47:29.240 --> 00:47:32.880
That's very exciting, because
possibly if they could remit

00:47:32.880 --> 00:47:35.750
their money back home--
send it home safely.

00:47:35.750 --> 00:47:38.510
Instead, now they're carrying
it all on their body.

00:47:38.510 --> 00:47:40.860
So everybody knows they
have all the money.

00:47:40.860 --> 00:47:43.950
They're ripped off all the time,
constantly, so they end

00:47:43.950 --> 00:47:46.720
up back home with nothing and
then it starts all over again.

00:47:46.720 --> 00:47:49.600
And sometimes I really believe
if we could get a safe way for

00:47:49.600 --> 00:47:52.620
that money to get home, they
could actually start a small

00:47:52.620 --> 00:47:55.710
business or they'd have some
capital to do something.

00:47:55.710 --> 00:47:58.260
But because we don't have that
set up very easily-- the

00:47:58.260 --> 00:48:00.570
banking system's so weak,
there's no banks in these

00:48:00.570 --> 00:48:04.620
rural areas, there's not a
remittance system, and so the

00:48:04.620 --> 00:48:07.750
cycle just keeps going
on and on again.

00:48:07.750 --> 00:48:10.870
It's very hard to break it.

00:48:10.870 --> 00:48:11.090
Yeah.

